    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "hfft"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "/"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "ihfft"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " are a pair analogous to "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "rfft"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "/"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "irfft"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", but for the\nopposite case: here the signal has Hermitian symmetry in the time\ndomain and is real in the frequency domain. So here it's "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "hfft"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " for\nwhich you must supply the length of the result if it is to be odd."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "even: "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "ihfft(hfft(a, 2*len(a) - 2)) == a"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": ", within roundoff error,"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "odd: "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "ihfft(hfft(a, 2*len(a) - 1)) == a"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": ", within roundoff error."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ordered": false,
          "type": "list"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The correct interpretation of the hermitian input depends on the length of\nthe original data, as given by "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ". This is because each input shape could\ncorrespond to either an odd or even length signal. By default, "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "hfft"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "\nassumes an even output length which puts the last entry at the Nyquist\nfrequency; aliasing with its symmetric counterpart. By Hermitian symmetry,\nthe value is thus treated as purely real. To avoid losing information, the\nshape of the full signal "
            },
            {
              "kind": "strong",
              "text": "must"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " be given."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import whest as we"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "signal = we.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 3, 2])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.fft.fft(signal)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([15.+0.j,  -4.+0.j,   0.+0.j,  -1.-0.j,   0.+0.j,  -4.+0.j]) # may vary"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.fft.hfft(signal[:4]) # Input first half of signal"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([15.,  -4.,   0.,  -1.,   0.,  -4.])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.fft.hfft(signal, 6)  # Input entire signal and truncate"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([15.,  -4.,   0.,  -1.,   0.,  -4.])"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "signal = we.array([[1, 1.j], [-1.j, 2]])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.conj(signal.T) - signal   # check Hermitian symmetry"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([[ 0.-0.j,  -0.+0.j], # may vary"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [ 0.+0.j,  0.-0.j]])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "freq_spectrum = we.fft.hfft(signal)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "freq_spectrum"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([[ 1.,  1.],"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "       [ 2., -2.]])"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
